item.description:
Annual Meeting of the Manchester Historic Association 

Friday, May 17, 2013

5:30 p.m.-7:30 p.m. 

FREE Admission

Pre-registration is required via Manchester History Network Meetup, by calling (603)622-7531 or by e-mail at history@manchesterhistoric.org.

This year's Annual Meeting will begin with the business meeting of the Manchester Historic Association, which will include the election of Trustees and Officers. This will be followed by a short talk by Manchester Historic Association staff who will tell the stories of the people portrayed in the new exhibit, "People you should know…Portraits from the Collection." The small exhibit opens to the public on Saturday, May 18, and will be on view in the Discovery Gallery until August 31, 2013.

Shown: Lieutenant Jean D. Grenier. Manchester's Grenier Army Air Force Base was named after Grenier in 1941.
